hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Babinet’s principle for complex amplitudes at point $P$:
$$U_{\mathrm{slit}}(P)+U_{\mathrm{strip}}(P)=U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}(P).$$
2. Given at the center of the pattern 
$$U_{\mathrm{slit}}=\frac{1+i}{2}\,U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}},$$
so
$$U_{\mathrm{strip}}=U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}-U_{\mathrm{slit}}
=U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}-\frac{1+i}{2}\,U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}
=\frac{2-(1+i)}{2}\,U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}
=\frac{1-i}{2}\,U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}.$$
3. The intensity ratio is
$$\frac{I_{\mathrm{strip}}}{I_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}}
=\frac{\bigl|U_{\mathrm{strip}}\bigr|^2}{\bigl|U_{\mathrm{unobstructed}}\bigr|^2}
=\Bigl|\frac{1-i}{2}\Bigr|^2
=\frac{(1)^2+(-1)^2}{4}
=\frac{2}{4}
=\frac12.$$
